HEADWORD: Oncometer
<hw>On*com"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ bulk +
<ets>-meter</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>An instrument for
measuring the variations in size of the internal organs of the body, as
the kidney, spleen, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

